# Project Guardrails

These apply to **every** interaction unless a human overrides for a narrow exception.

## Code quality

- Re-read the active task spec and RULEBOOK when starting substantive work.
- Zero `any` — use `unknown`, generics, or discriminated unions.
- Before claiming done: `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`, and `npm run test:unit` must pass (plus `format:check` when touching formatted files).
- Domain types under `src/backend/types/` stay read-only relative to external imports.

## Process

- **Triple deliverable**: each production `.ts` has `.reqs.md` and `.spec.ts` (template path: **`AGENTS.md`**).
- **Confidence**: &gt;80% proceed; 50–80% proceed and note in `decisions.md`; &lt;50% use the safe default and note.
- Avoid scope creep; defer work that belongs in another task.
- Commit after each completed subtask. **Do not commit** ephemeral automation state listed in **`AGENTS.md`**.

## RULEBOOK

- Canonical file: `docs/rulebook/RULEBOOK.md`. Category map: `docs/rulebook/RULEBOOK-INDEX.md`. Quick reference: `docs/rulebook/RULEBOOK-WORKFLOW-GUIDE.md`.
- Cite supporting rules in code: `// [ARCH-SOLID-003]`. If none apply, record in `decisions.md`.
- If an action would violate a **CRITICAL** rule, stop and ask the human before proceeding.

## Categories (summary)

| Category | Applies to |
|----------|------------|
| FORGE-OPS | Forge runtime, manifest, storage, limits |
| SEC-PRIV | Data, auth, scopes, secrets |
| ARCH-SOLID | Types, models, adapters, orchestration |
| TEST-QA | Anything shipping `.spec.ts` |
| GIT-CI | Tooling, CI/CD tasks |
| UI-ADS | Custom UI / ADS |
| ROVO-INTEG | Rovo adapter, resilience, triggers |
| GH-INTEG | GitHub integration, webhooks |

**Priority when rules conflict:** FORGE-OPS → SEC-PRIV → GH-INTEG → ARCH-SOLID → TEST-QA → GIT-CI → UI-ADS → ROVO-INTEG.

